%% Diagram: Partition Scenario — CP vs AP behaviour
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client
    participant N1 as Node A (saw write)
    participant N2 as Node B (isolated)

    rect rgba(46, 90, 136, 0.12)
    note over N1,N2: Partition: N1 ⇎ N2 cannot exchange messages
    end

    C->>N1: write(x = 1) [acked]
    C->>N2: read(x)

    alt CP system (linearizable)
        N2-->>C: ERROR / timeout — refuses to answer without quorum
        note right of N2: Sacrifices availability to preserve C
    else AP system (eventual)
        N2-->>C: x = 0 (stale) — local value
        note right of N2: Sacrifices consistency to preserve A
    end
